name: Elacor Pavis
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: So in this post I’d like to share 54 timeless, thought-provoking and inspiring quotes on education.

name: Belatius Wellawont
shortanswer: “It is impossible for a man to learn what he thinks he already knows.”

name: Cawtana Srinct
shortanswer: “Have you ever been at sea in a dense fog, when it seemed as if a tangible white darkness shut you in and the great ship, tense and anxious, groped her way toward the shore with plummet and sounding-line, and you waited with beating heart for something to happen? I was like that ship before my education began, only I was without compass or sounding line, and no way of knowing how near the harbor was. “Light! Give me light!” was the wordless cry of my soul, and the light of love shone on me in that very hour.”

name: Fughilda Bonshort
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “If the only tool you have is a hammer, you tend to see every problem as a nail.”

name: Nachranagare
shortanswer: “You can teach a student a lesson for a day; but if you can teach him to learn by creating curiosity, he will continue the learning process as long as he lives.”

name: Horolf  Weasley
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “Anyone who has never made a mistake has never tried anything new.”

name: Pille Torkis
shortanswer: “Aim for success, not perfection. Never give up your right to be wrong, because then you will lose the ability to learn new things and move forward with your life. Remember that fear always lurks behind perfectionism.”

name: S. Gawce
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “It is the mark of an educated mind to be able to entertain a thought without accepting it.”

name: Gatald
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “A teacher affects eternity; he can never tell where his influence stops.”

name: Milecs Brewett
shortanswer: “A man’s mind, stretched by new ideas, may never return to its original dimensions.”

name: Libert Stinglen
shortanswer: “Much education today is monumentally ineffective. All too often we are giving young people cut flowers when we should be teaching them to grow their own plants.”

name: Bloador
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “No man who worships education has got the best out of education…. Without a gentle contempt for education no man’s education is complete.”

name: Bole
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “To teach is to learn twice.”

name: Herky Wessley
shortanswer: “Why should society feel responsible only for the education of children, and not for the education of all adults of every age?”

name: Brand
shortanswer: “Keep away from people who try to belittle your ambitions. Small people always do that, but the really great make you feel that you, too, can become great.”

name: Zaberta Dirdle
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “When a subject becomes totally obsolete we make it a required course.”

name: Peleroppe Kerter
shortanswer: “The first problem for all of us, men and women, is not to learn, but to unlearn.”

name: Cartice Marge
shortanswer: “Children have never been very good at listening to their elders, but they have never failed to imitate them.”

name: Mernaga Jones
shortanswer: “Example is not the main thing in influencing others. It is the only thing.”

name: Groyle
shortanswer: “Education is a progressive discovery of our own ignorance.”

name: Marcole
shortanswer: “The aim of education should be to teach us rather how to think, than what to think — rather to improve our minds, so as to enable us to think for ourselves, than to load the memory with thoughts of other men.”

name: Sc Lyndrind
shortanswer: “Education is simply the soul of a society as it passes from one generation to another.”

name: Batrick Shalporke
shortanswer: “The difference between school and life? In school, you’re taught a lesson and then given a test. In life, you’re given a test that teaches you a lesson.”

name: Nilley Wolderidge
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “He who opens a school door, closes a prison.”

name: Molly Prewett
shortanswer: “If you think education is expensive, try ignorance.”

name: Varcus Flagg
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “Tell me and I’ll forget; show me and I may remember; involve me and I’ll understand.”

name: Herafle onge Bornagoon
shortanswer: “If a man is a fool, you don’t train him out of being a fool by sending him to university. You merely turn him into a trained fool, ten times more dangerous.”

name: Sathiria Tones
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “Nine tenths of education is encouragement.”

name: Augustus Rooks
shortanswer: “If someone is going down the wrong road, he doesn’t need motivation to speed him up. What he needs is education to turn him around.”

name: Angis Chamelle
shortanswer: “The most beautiful things in the creating of the child are his “mistakes.” The more a child’s work is full of these individual mistakes the more wonderful it is. And the more a teacher removes them from the child’s work the duller, more desolate and impersonal it becomes.”

name: Thous Crove
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “The modern world belongs to the half-educated, a rather difficult class, because they do not realize how little they know.”

name: Rosald Kengle
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “People learn something every day, and a lot of times it’s that what they learned the day before was wrong.”

name: Gonelda Michortan
interest1: helping children and teens become wiser consumers
shortanswer: “What does education often do? It makes a straight-cut ditch of a free, meandering brook.”

name: Abtrux Bolden
shortanswer: “Many highly intelligent people are poor thinkers. Many people of average intelligence are skilled thinkers. The power of the car is separate from the way the car is driven.”

name: S. Poffor
shortanswer: “Treat people as if they were what they ought to be, and you help them to become what they are capable of becoming.”

name: Carcus Blencon
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “Education cost money, but then so does ignorance.”

name: Pondlee
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “I’ve learned… that the best classroom in the world is at the feet of an elderly person.”

name: Ollator Bardbey
shortanswer: “If you are planning for a year, sow rice; if you are planning for a decade, plant trees; if you are planning for a lifetime, educate people.”

name: Richlad of Grangoon
shortanswer: “The whole purpose of education is to turn mirrors into windows.”

name: Norsely Plutt
shortanswer: “What sculpture is to a block of marble education is to the human soul.”

name: Negaline Jenserur
shortanswer: “Education makes a people easy to lead but difficult to drive: easy to govern, but impossible to enslave.”

name: Mortaguus Flamper
shortanswer: “The only thing that interferes with my learning is my education.”

name: Mornangua Mchinget
shortanswer: “The only person who is educated is the one who has learned how to learn …and change.”

name: Sannis Broche
shortanswer: “Education would be much more effective if its purpose was to ensure that by the time they leave school every boy and girl should know how much they do not know, and be imbued with a lifelong desire to know it.”

name: Bilbert the Wearrey
shortanswer: “If a man empties his purse into his head, no man can take it away from him. An investment in knowledge always pays the best interest.”

name: Gugan Prume
interest1: promoting civic engagement and political participation
shortanswer: “Do not train children to learning by force and harshness, but direct them to it by what amuses their minds, so that you may be better able to discover with accuracy the peculiar bent of the genius of each.”

name: Diger Dervins
shortanswer: “A well-educated mind will always have more questions than answers.”

name: Gumistor Keverill
shortanswer: “It is a thousand times better to have common sense without education than to have education without common sense.”
